{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":448,"text":"I'm going to go off script"},{"time":1715,"text":"and make Chris quite nervous here"},{"time":3766,"text":"by making this audience participation."},{"time":6114,"text":"All right. Are you with me? Yeah. Yeah. All right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9297,"text":"So what I'd like to do is have you raise your hand"},{"time":11741,"text":"if you've ever heard a\nheterosexual couple having sex."},{"time":15797,"text":"Could be the neighbors, hotel room,"},{"time":18348,"text":"your parents. Sorry."},{"time":20355,"text":"Okay. Pretty much everybody."},{"time":22107,"text":"Now raise your hand if the man was making"},{"time":23934,"text":"more noise than the woman."},{"time":27363,"text":"I see one guy there."},{"time":29676,"text":"It doesn't count if it was you, sir."},{"time":31923,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":32938,"text":"So his hand's down. And one woman. Okay."},{"time":36448,"text":"Sitting next to a loud guy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38524,"text":"Now what does this tell us?"},{"time":40148,"text":"It tells us that human beings"},{"time":41994,"text":"make noise when they have sex,"},{"time":43362,"text":"and it's generally the woman who makes more noise."},{"time":45488,"text":"This is known as female copulatory vocalization"},{"time":48542,"text":"to the clipboard crowd."},{"time":49965,"text":"I wasn't even going to mention this,"},{"time":51596,"text":"but somebody told me that Meg Ryan might be here,"},{"time":54537,"text":"and she is the world's most famous"},{"time":57141,"text":"female copulatory vocalizer."},{"time":59090,"text":"So I thought, got to talk about that."},{"time":61490,"text":"We'll get back to that a little bit later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64203,"text":"Let me start by saying human beings"},{"time":66168,"text":"are not descended from apes,"},{"time":68269,"text":"despite what you may have heard. We are apes."},{"time":70501,"text":"We are more closely related\nto the chimp and the bonobo"},{"time":73337,"text":"than the African elephant is to the Indian elephant,"},{"time":76717,"text":"as Jared Diamond pointed\nout in one of his early books."},{"time":79915,"text":"We're more closely related to chimps and bonobos"},{"time":84110,"text":"than chimps and bonobos are related"},{"time":85611,"text":"to any other primate --"},{"time":87273,"text":"gorillas, orangutans, what have you."},{"time":89549,"text":"So we're extremely closely related to them,"},{"time":92796,"text":"and as you'll see in terms of our behavior,"},{"time":95222,"text":"we've got some relationship as well."},{"time":97589,"text":"So what I'm asking today, the question"},{"time":99508,"text":"I want to explore with you today is,"},{"time":102570,"text":"what kind of ape are we in terms of our sexuality?"},{"time":106738,"text":"Now, since Darwin's day there's been"},{"time":108956,"text":"what Cacilda and I have called"},{"time":110458,"text":"the standard narrative of human sexual evolution,"},{"time":113144,"text":"and you're all familiar with it,"},{"time":114698,"text":"even if you haven't read this stuff."},{"time":117261,"text":"The idea is that, as part of human nature,"},{"time":120329,"text":"from the beginning of our species' time,"},{"time":122318,"text":"men have sort of leased\nwomen's reproductive potential"},{"time":126812,"text":"by providing them with certain goods and services."},{"time":130207,"text":"Generally we're talking about meat, shelter, status,"},{"time":133877,"text":"protection, things like that."},{"time":136508,"text":"And in exchange, women have offered fidelity,"},{"time":138843,"text":"or at least a promise of fidelity."},{"time":141221,"text":"Now this sets men and women up\nin an oppositional relationship."},{"time":145491,"text":"The war between the sexes is built right into\nour DNA, according to this vision. Right?"},{"time":151434,"text":"What Cacilda and I have argued is that no,"},{"time":155371,"text":"this economic relationship,"},{"time":157812,"text":"this oppositional relationship,"},{"time":159637,"text":"is actually an artifact of agriculture,"},{"time":162262,"text":"which only arose about 10,000\nyears ago at the earliest."},{"time":165938,"text":"Anatomically modern human beings"},{"time":168105,"text":"have been around for about 200,000 years,"},{"time":171104,"text":"so we're talking about five percent, at most,"},{"time":174726,"text":"of our time as a modern, distinct species."},{"time":178414,"text":"So before agriculture,"},{"time":181948,"text":"before the agricultural revolution,"},{"time":183953,"text":"it's important to understand that human beings"},{"time":186064,"text":"lived in hunter-gatherer groups that are"},{"time":189398,"text":"characterized wherever they're found in the world"},{"time":192414,"text":"by what anthropologists called fierce egalitarianism."},{"time":197005,"text":"They not only share things,"},{"time":198873,"text":"they demand that things be shared:"},{"time":201382,"text":"meat, shelter, protection, all these things"},{"time":203641,"text":"that were supposedly being traded to women"},{"time":206650,"text":"for their sexual fidelity, it turns out,"},{"time":209480,"text":"are shared widely among these societies."},{"time":212210,"text":"Now I'm not saying that our ancestors"},{"time":214398,"text":"were noble savages, and I'm not saying"},{"time":216359,"text":"modern day hunter-gatherers\nare noble savages either."},{"time":219155,"text":"What I'm saying is that this is simply"},{"time":221166,"text":"the best way to mitigate risk"},{"time":223606,"text":"in a foraging context."},{"time":225536,"text":"And there's really no argument\nabout this among anthropologists."},{"time":228652,"text":"All Cacilda and I have done is extend\nthis sharing behavior to sexuality."},{"time":233216,"text":"So we've argued that human sexuality"},{"time":235651,"text":"has essentially evolved, until agriculture,"},{"time":240135,"text":"as a way of establishing and maintaining"},{"time":243281,"text":"the complex, flexible social systems, networks,"},{"time":247007,"text":"that our ancestors were very good at,"},{"time":249918,"text":"and that's why our species has survived so well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254534,"text":"Now, this makes some people uncomfortable,"},{"time":256751,"text":"and so I always need to take \na moment in these talks"},{"time":259136,"text":"to say, listen,"},{"time":260980,"text":"I'm saying our ancestors were promiscuous,"},{"time":263623,"text":"but I'm not saying they were\nhaving sex with strangers."},{"time":265958,"text":"There were no strangers. Right?"},{"time":267984,"text":"In a hunter-gatherer band, there are no strangers."},{"time":269828,"text":"You've known these people your entire life."},{"time":271817,"text":"So I'm saying, yes, there were\noverlapping sexual relationships,"},{"time":275276,"text":"that our ancestors probably had\nseveral different sexual relationships"},{"time":279583,"text":"going on at any given moment in their adult lives."},{"time":282970,"text":"But I'm not saying they were\nhaving sex with strangers."},{"time":285373,"text":"I'm not saying that they didn't love the\npeople they were having sex with."},{"time":288484,"text":"And I'm not saying there was\nno pair-bonding going on."},{"time":291389,"text":"I'm just saying it wasn't sexually exclusive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294475,"text":"And those of us who have\nchosen to be monogamous --"},{"time":298159,"text":"my parents, for example, have been married"},{"time":300497,"text":"for 52 years monogamously,"},{"time":303005,"text":"and if it wasn't monogamously, Mom and Dad,"},{"time":305367,"text":"I don't want to hear about itâ€”"},{"time":307714,"text":"I'm not criticizing this and I'm not saying"},{"time":310106,"text":"there's anything wrong with this."},{"time":311662,"text":"What I'm saying is that to argue"},{"time":313821,"text":"that our ancestors were sexual omnivores"},{"time":318495,"text":"is no more a criticism of monogamy"},{"time":320782,"text":"than to argue that our ancestors\nwere dietary omnivores"},{"time":324250,"text":"is a criticism of vegetarianism."},{"time":327573,"text":"You can choose to be a vegetarian,"},{"time":329454,"text":"but don't think that just because\nyou've made that decision,"},{"time":332198,"text":"bacon suddenly stops smelling good."},{"time":334990,"text":"Okay? So this is my point."},{"time":337677,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":340028,"text":"That one took a minute to sink in, huh?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":343649,"text":"Now, in addition to being a great genius,"},{"time":345979,"text":"a wonderful man, a wonderful husband,"},{"time":348044,"text":"a wonderful father, Charles Darwin"},{"time":349824,"text":"was also a world-class Victorian prude."},{"time":353936,"text":"All right? He was perplexed"},{"time":355876,"text":"by the sexual swellings of certain primates,"},{"time":358486,"text":"including chimps and bonobos,"},{"time":360029,"text":"because these sexual swellings tend to provoke"},{"time":362567,"text":"many males to mate with the females."},{"time":365159,"text":"So he couldn't understand why on Earth would\nthe female have developed this thing"},{"time":368330,"text":"if all they were supposed to be doing\nis forming their pair bond, right?"},{"time":372259,"text":"Chimps and bonobos, Darwin didn't really know this,"},{"time":374698,"text":"but chimps and bonobos mate"},{"time":376646,"text":"one to four times per hour"},{"time":378300,"text":"with up to a dozen males per day"},{"time":381716,"text":"when they have their sexual swellings."},{"time":384332,"text":"Interestingly, chimps have sexual swellings"},{"time":386987,"text":"through 40 percent, roughly,"},{"time":388789,"text":"of their menstrual cycle,"},{"time":390674,"text":"bonobos 90 percent,"},{"time":393374,"text":"and humans are among the\nonly species on the planet"},{"time":396796,"text":"where the female is available for sex"},{"time":398898,"text":"throughout the menstrual cycle,"},{"time":400886,"text":"whether she's menstruating,\nwhether she's post-menopausal,"},{"time":403630,"text":"whether she's already pregnant."},{"time":404941,"text":"This is vanishingly rare among mammals."},{"time":408785,"text":"So it's a very interesting aspect of human sexuality."},{"time":412578,"text":"Now, Darwin ignored the reflections"},{"time":415253,"text":"of the sexual swelling in his own day,"},{"time":418821,"text":"as scientists tend to do sometimes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422452,"text":"So what we're talking about is sperm competition."},{"time":424957,"text":"Now the average human ejaculate\nhas about 300 million sperm cells,"},{"time":428367,"text":"so it's already a competitive environment."},{"time":430797,"text":"The question is whether these sperm are \ncompeting against other men's sperm"},{"time":434030,"text":"or just their own."},{"time":435815,"text":"There's a lot to talk about in this chart."},{"time":437921,"text":"The one thing I'll call your attention to right away"},{"time":440096,"text":"is the little musical note above the\nfemale chimp and bonobo and human."},{"time":444138,"text":"That indicates female copulatory vocalization."},{"time":447439,"text":"Just look at the numbers."},{"time":449041,"text":"The average human has sex"},{"time":451237,"text":"about 1,000 times per birth."},{"time":454879,"text":"If that number seems high for some of you,"},{"time":457052,"text":"I assure you it seems low for others in the room."},{"time":460265,"text":"We share that ratio with chimps and bonobos."},{"time":463215,"text":"We don't share it with the other three apes,"},{"time":465517,"text":"the gorilla, the orangutan and the gibbon,"},{"time":467773,"text":"who are more typical of mammals,"},{"time":469434,"text":"having sex only about a dozen times per birth."},{"time":472626,"text":"Humans and bonobos are the only \nanimals that have sex face-to-face"},{"time":476847,"text":"when both of them are alive."},{"time":479253,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":483895,"text":"And you'll see that the human, chimp and bonobo"},{"time":487066,"text":"all have external testicles, which in our book"},{"time":489462,"text":"we equate to a special fridge you have in the garage"},{"time":493450,"text":"just for beer."},{"time":495710,"text":"If you're the kind of guy who has a beer fridge"},{"time":498436,"text":"in the garage, you expect a party to happen"},{"time":500778,"text":"at any moment, and you need to be ready."},{"time":502567,"text":"That's what the external testicles are."},{"time":504722,"text":"They keep the sperm cells cool"},{"time":507132,"text":"so you can have frequent ejaculations."},{"time":509350,"text":"I'm sorry. It's true."},{"time":513089,"text":"The human, some of you will be happy to hear,"},{"time":516178,"text":"has the largest, thickest penis of any primate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518989,"text":"Now, this evidence goes way beyond anatomy."},{"time":521499,"text":"It goes into anthropology as well."},{"time":524060,"text":"Historical records are full of accounts of people"},{"time":526677,"text":"around the world who have sexual practices"},{"time":528486,"text":"that should be impossible"},{"time":530116,"text":"given what we have assumed\nabout human sexual evolution."},{"time":534042,"text":"These women are the Mosuo\nfrom southwestern China."},{"time":536742,"text":"In their society, everyone, men and women,"},{"time":539309,"text":"are completely sexually autonomous."},{"time":541050,"text":"There's no shame associated with sexual behavior."},{"time":544009,"text":"Women have hundreds of partners."},{"time":546255,"text":"It doesn't matter. Nobody cares.\nNobody gossips. It's not an issue."},{"time":549437,"text":"When the woman becomes pregnant,"},{"time":551233,"text":"the child is cared for by her, \nher sisters, and her brothers."},{"time":554091,"text":"The biological father is a nonissue."},{"time":556930,"text":"On the other side of the planet, in the Amazon,"},{"time":559336,"text":"we've got many tribes which practice"},{"time":562205,"text":"what anthropologists call partible paternity."},{"time":564937,"text":"These people actually believe --"},{"time":567534,"text":"and they have no contact among them,"},{"time":569249,"text":"no common language or anything,"},{"time":570905,"text":"so it's not an idea that spread,"},{"time":572642,"text":"it's an idea that's arisen around the world --"},{"time":574779,"text":"they believe that a fetus is literally made"},{"time":576936,"text":"of accumulated semen."},{"time":579212,"text":"So a woman who wants to have a child"},{"time":581200,"text":"who's smart and funny and strong"},{"time":583032,"text":"makes sure she has lots of sex with the smart guy,"},{"time":585163,"text":"the funny guy and the strong guy,"},{"time":587107,"text":"to get the essence of each of\nthese men into the baby,"},{"time":589331,"text":"and then when the child is born,"},{"time":591843,"text":"these different men will come forward"},{"time":593985,"text":"and acknowledge their paternity of the child."},{"time":596855,"text":"So paternity is actually sort of a team endeavor"},{"time":599693,"text":"in this society."},{"time":601309,"text":"So there are all sorts of examples like this"},{"time":603297,"text":"that we go through in the book."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605747,"text":"Now, why does this matter?"},{"time":609207,"text":"Edward Wilson says we need to understand"},{"time":611767,"text":"that human sexuality is first a bonding device"},{"time":614813,"text":"and only secondarily procreation."},{"time":617648,"text":"I think that's true. This matters because"},{"time":619832,"text":"our evolved sexuality is in direct conflict"},{"time":622870,"text":"with many aspects of the modern world."},{"time":625457,"text":"The contradictions between what we're told"},{"time":627595,"text":"we should feel and what we actually do feel"},{"time":631022,"text":"generates a huge amount of unnecessary suffering."},{"time":636159,"text":"My hope is that a more accurate,"},{"time":638575,"text":"updated understanding of human sexuality"},{"time":640950,"text":"will lead us to have greater tolerance for ourselves,"},{"time":643970,"text":"for each other,"},{"time":645567,"text":"greater respect for unconventional\nrelationship configurations"},{"time":649190,"text":"like same-sex marriage or polyamorous unions,"},{"time":654471,"text":"and that we'll finally put to rest the idea"},{"time":657819,"text":"that men have some innate, instinctive right"},{"time":660393,"text":"to monitor and control women's sexual behavior."},{"time":664621,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":667613,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":669767,"text":"And we'll see that it's not only gay people"},{"time":672023,"text":"that have to come out of the closet."},{"time":673692,"text":"We all have closets we have to come out of. Right?"},{"time":677221,"text":"And when we do come out of those closets,"},{"time":678982,"text":"we'll recognize that our fight is not with each other,"},{"time":682541,"text":"our fight is with an outdated, \nVictorian sense of human sexuality"},{"time":687045,"text":"that conflates desire with property rights,"},{"time":690600,"text":"generates shame and confusion"},{"time":693365,"text":"in place of understanding and empathy."},{"time":696200,"text":"It's time we moved beyond Mars and Venus,"},{"time":698916,"text":"because the truth is"},{"time":700646,"text":"that men are from Africa"},{"time":701983,"text":"and women are from Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703979,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705924,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":714530,"text":"Chris Anderson: Thank you.\nChristopher Ryan: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717024,"text":"CA: So a question."},{"time":718766,"text":"It's so perplexing, trying to use arguments"},{"time":722665,"text":"about evolutionary history"},{"time":725732,"text":"to turn that into what we ought to do today."},{"time":728316,"text":"Someone could give a talk and say,"},{"time":730722,"text":"look at us, we've got these really sharp teeth"},{"time":733467,"text":"and muscles and a brain that's really good"},{"time":735194,"text":"at throwing weapons,"},{"time":736755,"text":"and if you look at lots of societies around the world,"},{"time":739819,"text":"you'll see very high rates of violence."},{"time":742105,"text":"Nonviolence is a choice like vegetarianism,"},{"time":745274,"text":"but it's not who you are."},{"time":747418,"text":"How is that different"},{"time":749468,"text":"from the talk you gave?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":752833,"text":"CR: Well first of all, the evidence"},{"time":756017,"text":"for high levels of violence in prehistory"},{"time":758792,"text":"is very debatable."},{"time":761398,"text":"But that's just an example."},{"time":763599,"text":"Certainly, you know, lots of people say to me,"},{"time":767203,"text":"just because we lived a certain way in the past"},{"time":769743,"text":"doesn't mean we should live that \nway now, and I agree with that."},{"time":772942,"text":"Everyone has to respond to the modern world."},{"time":775469,"text":"But the body does have its inherent"},{"time":779891,"text":"evolved trajectories."},{"time":782748,"text":"And so you could live on\nMcDonald's and milkshakes,"},{"time":786228,"text":"but your body will rebel against \nthat. We have appetites."},{"time":789702,"text":"I think it was Schopenhauer who said,"},{"time":791390,"text":"a person can do what they want"},{"time":794254,"text":"but not want what they want."},{"time":796311,"text":"And so what I'm arguing against"},{"time":798034,"text":"is the shame that's associated with desires."},{"time":800498,"text":"It's the idea that if you love your husband or wife"},{"time":803857,"text":"but you still are attracted to other people,"},{"time":806067,"text":"there's something wrong with you,"},{"time":807566,"text":"there's something wrong with your marriage,"},{"time":809503,"text":"something wrong with your partner."},{"time":810963,"text":"I think a lot of families are fractured"},{"time":812986,"text":"by unrealistic expectations"},{"time":814971,"text":"that are based upon this false\nvision of human sexuality."},{"time":818016,"text":"That's what I'm trying to get at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819480,"text":"CA: Thank you. Communicated\npowerfully. Thanks a lot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821979,"text":"CR: Thank you, Chris.\n(Applause)"}]}]}